<MudPaper Class="px-6 py-4 ma-2" Elevation="4">
    <MudText Typo="Typo.h4">Leveraging Tools for Agile Frameworks</MudText>
    <MudText Typo="Typo.subtitle1" Class="mb-4">Tools like Jira Software can help teams implement and manage Agile frameworks like Scrum and Kanban. By using features like Scrum and Kanban boards, teams can tailor these frameworks to their specific workflows, enhancing their ability to deliver value effectively.</MudText>

    <MudText Typo="Typo.h5" Class="mt-4">Understanding Kanban Boards</MudText>
    <MudText Typo="Typo.body1" Class="mb-4">A Kanban board is a visual tool used to manage and optimize workflow. It displays work items as cards moving across columns that represent stages in a workflow, such as "To Do," "In Progress," "In Review," and "Done." This visual representation helps teams track progress, identify bottlenecks, and maintain a shared understanding of the project status.</MudText>

    <MudText Typo="Typo.h5" Class="mt-4">Supporting Agile Development</MudText>
    <MudText Typo="Typo.body1" Class="mb-4">Kanban boards align with Agile principles by visualizing the flow of work, promoting transparency, and enabling teams to adapt to changes quickly. This iterative process supports Agile's emphasis on flexibility and responsiveness.</MudText>

    <MudText Typo="Typo.h5" Class="mt-4">Benefits of Kanban Boards</MudText>
    <MudList T="string" Class="pl-4">
        <MudListItem>• Visualizing Workflow: Provides a clear view of work progress and helps identify bottlenecks.</MudListItem>
        <MudListItem>• WIP Limits: Encourages teams to finish work before starting new tasks, improving flow.</MudListItem>
        <MudListItem>• Improved Team Productivity: Enhances team communication and collaboration, resulting in better efficiency.</MudListItem>
        <MudListItem>• Continuous Delivery: Supports frequent, reliable software releases by optimizing workflow and removing bottlenecks.</MudListItem>
    </MudList>

    <MudText Typo="Typo.h5" Class="mt-4">Use Cases for Kanban Boards</MudText>
    <MudText Typo="Typo.body1" Class="mb-4">Organizations use Kanban boards for a variety of purposes, from software development to IT services. Tools like Jira Software offer customizable Kanban boards to reflect unique workflows, manage WIP, and gain insights into process optimization.</MudText>
</MudPaper>

